Before Install You Must Install NetworkManager By Using sudo pacman -S networkmanager
For Audio Systems
Pipewire
sudo pacman -S pipewire pipewire-alsa pipewire-pulse pipewire-jack wireplumber
Pulseaudio
sudo pacman -S pulseaudio pulseaudio-alsa
pulseaudio --start
Getting A Graphical Environment Which You Must And Recommended To use LXDE Because Its Faster On Old Hardware And Its Recommended To Install LXDM Because LXDM (LXDE Display Manager) is a lightweight display manager designed for low-resource environments.
Specifically developed for the LXDE desktop environment
it provides a fast, GTK+-based graphical login interface that is well-suited for older machines or systems requiring minimal overhead 
if theres lightdm sudo pacman -Rns lightdm lightdm-gtk-greeter
If Theres No Lightdm Enable LXDM Services
sudo systemctl enable lxdm.service
sudo systemctl start lxdm.service
If It Didnt Start reboot using sudo reboot
But If It Didnt Login To Lxde
However You Can Install Other Desktop Environment Like GNOME KDE Plasma XFCE MATE LXQT And More
sudo pacman -S lxde lxdm
After You Install The Desktop Environment Install Firefox using sudo pacman -S firefox
Then Go To https://github.com/Haikal02-alt/HS-DOS
Then Download The HS-DOS Logo On readme
Then Save Image As Then if You See 543402333-30d3a74a-3e27-448e-9ae9-0e927a96ab00.png Rename It To hsdos-logo.png then save it to download
Then sudo mv /home/yourname/Downloads/hsdos-logo.png /usr/share/pixmaps
Then sudo cp /usr/share/pixmaps/hsdos-logo.png /usr/share/pixmaps/archlinux-logo.png
Then sudo cp /usr/share/pixmaps/hsdos-logo.png /usr/share/pixmaps/archlinux-logo.svg
Then sudo cp /usr/share/pixmaps/hsdos-logo.png /usr/share/pixmaps/archlinux-logo-text.svg
Then sudo cp /usr/share/pixmaps/hsdos-logo.png /usr/share/pixmaps/archlinux-logo-text-dark.svg

Installing KDE Plasma

Install With sudo pacman -S
sudo pacman -S plasma konsole dolphin
Enable Display Manager
sudo pacman -S sddm
sudo systemctl enable sddm
sudo systemctl start sddm

Open Konsole
Then run sudo nano /etc/os-release
Then Change LOGO=archlinux-logo To LOGO=/usr/share/pixmaps/hsdos-logo.png
Ctrl X Y Enter

Go To System settings Then Notifications Then System Notifications Then Play A Sound On Login And Logout Then Click apply

Installing GNOME

Install Gnome
sudo pacman -S gnome gnome-extra
Enable Services
sudo systemctl enable gdm.service --force
sudo systemctl start gdm.service
sudo nano /etc/os-release
Change LOGO=archlinux-logo To LOGO=/usr/share/pixmaps/hsdos-logo.png

Other Desktop Environment

Cinnamon
sudo pacman -S cinnamon
XFCE
sudo pacman -S xfce4
LXQt
sudo pacman -S lxqt
MATE
sudo pacman -S mate mate-extra

Popular Tiling & Lightweight Window Managers

Hyprland (Wayland compositor)
sudo pacman -S hyprland
Sway (Wayland i3-like compositor)
sudo pacman -S sway
i3wm
sudo pacman -S i3-wm i3status dmenu
MangoWM (community/AUR, not in official repos)  
Install via AUR helper (e.g., yay)
yay -S mangowm
IceWM
sudo pacman -S icewm

Other Display Managers

LightDM
sudo pacman -S lightdm lightdm-gtk-greeter
sudo systemctl enable lightdm
